Group A: Short Questions (2 Marks)
1. Define Information Architecture (IA).
Information Architecture is the practice of organizing, structuring, 
and labeling content on a website or application in a clear and logical way, 
so that users can easily find information and navigate the system efficiently.

2. What is a ”Wireframe”?
A wireframe is a simple visual guide or blueprint of a website’s layout that 
shows the arrangement of elements like headers, menus, content sections, and buttons without design details. 
It focuses on structure and functionality rather than colors, fonts, or images.

3. Explain the concept of ”Cognitive Friction” in web design.
Cognitive friction refers to the mental effort or difficulty a user experiences when interacting with a website or application. 
It occurs when navigation is confusing, information is unclear, or tasks are complicated, causing frustration and slowing down user actions. 
Good web design minimizes cognitive friction by providing clear layouts, intuitive navigation, and simple instructions.

4. Why should URL slugs use hyphens instead of underscores?
URL slugs should use hyphens (-) instead of underscores (_) because:
	1.	Search Engine Optimization (SEO): Search engines like Google treat hyphens as word separators, making URLs more readable and improving search rankings.
	2.	Readability: Hyphens are easier for users to read and understand, e.g., www.example.com/web-design-tips is clearer than www.example.com/web_design_tips.
	3.	Consistency: Hyphens are widely accepted as the standard for web URLs, ensuring better compatibility and user experience.


