 │    ├─ Undergraduate
 │    └─ Graduate
 ├─ Departments
 │    ├─ Computer Science
 │    ├─ Physics
 │    └─ Chemistry
 ├─ Alumni
 │    ├─ Events
 │    └─ Achievements
 └─ News
      ├─ Campus News
      └─ Research Updates
This structure organizes content clearly and supports intuitive navigation for students, faculty, and visitors.

9. A user visits a website but leaves within 10 seconds because they cannot find the navigation
menu, which is hidden behind a small icon on a desktop screen. Analyze this design failure
using the ”KISS” (Keep It Simple) principle.
The KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid) principle emphasizes that designs should be simple, clear, and intuitive for users.

Design Failure:
	•	Hiding the navigation menu behind a small icon on a desktop screen adds unnecessary complexity.
	•	Users cannot easily find or access important links, causing frustration.
	•	The website fails to provide straightforward and obvious navigation, leading to a high bounce rate.

Lesson:
Following the KISS principle, the navigation menu should be visible and easy to use, 
especially on larger screens, ensuring users can find information quickly without extra effort. 
Simple, clear design enhances usability and user satisfaction.

10. An e-commerce website has a URL structure like www.shop.com/prod?id=55&cat=9. Ex-
plain why this is bad for both users and Search Engines (SEO), and propose a better
structure using Page Slugs.
The URL www.shop.com/prod?id=55&cat=9 is bad for both users and SEO because:
	1.	Not User-Friendly: It’s difficult to read, remember, or understand what the page is about.
	2.	Poor SEO: Search engines cannot easily interpret the keywords, reducing the page’s ranking potential.
	3.	Lacks Clarity: Does not describe the product or category, making sharing and linking less effective.

Better Structure Using Page Slugs:

Use a descriptive, readable URL with hyphens:
www.shop.com/electronics/smartphone-xyz
Benefits:
	•	Readable & Memorable: Users can understand the content from the URL.
	•	SEO-Friendly: Keywords like “electronics” and “smartphone-xyz” improve search rankings.
•	Clean & Shareable: Easy to share on social media or in emails.
